# TypeScript & Biome Style Rules

## TypeScript
- Strict mode is on (`strict`, `noUnusedLocals`, `noUnusedParameters`,
  `noFallthroughCasesInSwitch`, `noUncheckedSideEffectImports`). Don't write code that
  requires loosening these.
- Path alias `@/*` maps to each app's `src/*` — use it instead of deep relative
  imports (`../../..`) within an app.
- `moduleResolution: bundler`, `noEmit: true` — type checking is separate from
  building (`tsc --noEmit` runs before `vite build` in each app's `build` script).

## Code style (enforced by Biome, `biome.json` at repo root)
- 2-space indentation, 100-char line width
- Double quotes, semicolons always
- Organize imports is enabled — don't hand-order imports against what Biome would produce
- Run `pnpm lint` (check) or `pnpm lint:fix` (autofix) rather than reformatting by hand
- Don't introduce ESLint, Prettier, or their config files — this repo standardized on Biome
